==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Copyhold
<hw>Cop"y*hold`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A tenure of estate by copy of court roll; or a tenure
for which the tenant has nothing to show, except the rolls made by the
steward of the lord's court.</def> <au>Blackstone.</au> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Land held in copyhold.</def> <au>Milton.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <ex>Copyholds</ex> do not exist in the United
States.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Copyholder</ent>⟦br⟧
